r   read 
w   write
x   execute 

u   user 
g   group
o   other (everyone)

0   no permission   ---
1   execute         --x 
2   write           -w-
3   execute write   -wx
4   read            r--
5   read execute    r-x 
6   read write      rw-
7   read write exe  rwx

digits for user group other 


user | group | other 
-rwxrwxrwx

--change permission:
chmod

-- change permission of a group write
chmod g-w filename

-- remove read permission for everyone
chmod a-r filename

-- remove write permission for an user 
chmod u-w filename

-- add permision for an user
chmod u+rw filename

-- add read permission to everyone 
chmod ugo+r filename 
chmod 444 filename 

